p.verse:
17 I applied my mind to know wisdom and knowledge,
madness and folly;
I learned that this too is a pursuit of the wind.

1 I
                said to myself, “Go ahead, I will test you with pleasure;
                enjoy what is good.” But it turned out to be futile.

9
                So I became great and surpassed all who were before me in Jerusalem;
                my wisdom also remained with me.

23 For all his days are filled with grief, and his occupation is sorrowful;
even at night, his mind does not rest.
This too is futile.

17 I observed all the work of God and concluded that a person is unable to discover the work that
is done under the sun. Even though a person labors hard to explore it, he cannot find it;
even if a wise person claims to know it, he is unable to discover it.
